Jenkara is a 3D modeler for GTK+ based on MilkShape 3D.  It is written with 
tools that should compile on Win32 and Linux.  It is tested mainly on Linux
(Debian Sid), and is currently in early stages.

Features:
Importing of Quake .mdl models
Rotation, Zooming
3D Textured & Wireframe views
2D Wireframe Views from Top, Bottom, Left, Right Front & Back

